h%20%7C%20What%20the%20Escalating%20War%20Means%20For%20Netanyahu%2C%20Hamas%2C%20Arab%20Countries%20And%20the%20World%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F10204347%2Fkttt.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Gideon%20Rachman%2C%20the%20chief%20foreign%20affairs%20commentator%20of%3Cem%3E%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20discusses%20the%20implications%20and%20consequences%20of%20the%20present%20crisis%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20amidst%20the%20escalating%20war%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas.%20He%20speaks%20with%20specific%20reference%20to%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20Hamas%2C%20the%20Arab%20countries%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%2C%20particularly%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F3ud__248-KY%3Fsi%3DAvwG_wlV7zbKxfvn%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EBelow%20is%20the%20list%20of%20questions%20that%20are%20posed%20to%20Rachman.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E1)%20Let%E2%80%99s%20start%20with%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20before%20we%20broaden%20our%20discussion%20and%20talk%20about%20the%20other%20people%20and%20organisations%20affected%20by%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict.%20In%20an%20op-ed%20for%20your%20paper%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20yesterday%20(October%209)%20you%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CNetanyahu%E2%80%99s%20entire%20strategy%20towards%20the%20Palestinians%20now%20looks%20like%20a%20failure.%E2%80%9D%20Is%20that%20because%20his%20aim%20was%20to%20shrink%20the%20conflict%20with%20the%20Palestinians%20and%20push%20it%20to%20one%20side%20as%20he%20got%20on%20with%20building%20relationships%20with%20the%20Arab%20countries%20of%20the%20region%3F%20But%20now%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20has%20forced%20the%20Palestinian%20issue%20back%20to%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20agenda%20in%20a%20way%20that%20it%20simply%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20sidelined%20or%20diminished%20any%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E2)%20The%20question%20is%20what%20does%20Netanyahu%20do%20now%3F%20He%E2%80%99s%20promised%20a%20massive%20retaliation%20which%20is%20already%20underway.%20But%20the%20problem%20is%2C%20as%20you%20write%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Israeli%20government%20does%20not%20yet%20have%20any%20vision%20that%20goes%20beyond%20killing%20Hamas%20leaders.%E2%80%9D%20So%20beyond%20the%20principle%20revenge%20is%20sweet%20is%20there%20a%20danger%20this%20could%20exacerbate%20the%20crisis%20rather%20than%20create%20political%20space%20for%20him%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E3)%20Yesterday%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20Israel%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Netanyahu%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20going%20to%20change%20the%20Middle%20East.%E2%80%9D%20Is%20that%20the%20sort%20of%20threat%20or%20challenge%20that%20could%20draw%20Hezbollah%20and%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20Iran%2C%20more%20directly%20into%20this%20conflict%3F%20So%20far%20Hezbollah%20has%20only%20fired%20a%20few%20rockets%20and%20the%20US%20says%20there%20is%20%E2%80%9Cno%20direct%20evidence%20of%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20role%E2%80%9D.%20So%20is%20Netanyahu%20inviting%20trouble%20when%20he%20says%20he%E2%80%99s%20going%20to%20change%20the%20Middle%20East%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E4)%20One%20more%20question%20about%20Netanyahu.%20This%20time%20it%E2%80%99s%20about%20his%20personal%20future.%20On%20October%208%2C%20%3Cem%3EHaaretz%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20possibly%20the%20most%20influential%20paper%20in%20Israel%2C%20squarely%20blamed%20him%20for%20what%20it%20calls%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20disaster%20that%20befell%20Israel%E2%80%9D%20and%20it%20specifically%20accused%20his%20government%20%E2%80%9Cof%20annexation%20and%20dispossession%E2%80%9D%20and%20his%20foreign%20policy%20of%20ignoring%20the%20existence%20and%20rights%20of%20Palestinians.%20On%20October%209%2C%20it%20warned%20against%20%E2%80%9Ccampaigns%20of%20vengeance%20and%20the%20commission%20of%20war%20crimes.%E2%80%9D%20So%20even%20if%20in%20the%20immediate%20term%20politicians%20and%20the%20country%20unite%20behind%20Netanyahu%2C%20is%20the%20end%20of%20his%20political%20career%20also%20in%20sight%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E5)%20Let%E2%80%99s%20come%20to%20Hamas.%20Although%20it%E2%80%99s%20clearly%20brought%20down%20the%20wrath%20of%20Israel%20on%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza%2C%20who%20are%20not%20only%20being%20badly%20bombed%20but%20denied%20electricity%2C%20water%2C%20fuel%20and%20food%20supplies%2C%20can%20they%20claim%20credit%20for%20two%20things%3F%20Restoring%20the%20Palestinian%20issue%20to%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20agenda%20and%2C%20perhaps%2C%20replacing%20the%20Palestine%20Authority%20and%20Fatah%20as%20the%20main%20representative%20of%20the%20Palestine%20cause%3F%20Or%20would%20you%20disagree%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E6)%20The%20other%20question%20about%20Hamas%20is%20how%20is%20it%20viewed%20by%20the%20Arab%20governments%20of%20the%20Middle%20East.%20Has%20this%20dramatic%20action%20won%20a%20measure%20of%20respect%20or%20only%20increased%20their%20apprehensions%20and%20concerns%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E7)%20Let%E2%80%99s%20come%20to%20the%20countries%20of%20the%20region.%20Crown%20Prince%20Mohammed%20bin%20Salman%20has%20said%20Saudi%20Arabia%20%E2%80%9Cstands%20by%20the%20Palestine%20people%20to%20achieve%20their%20legitimate%20rights%20to%20a%20decent%20life.%E2%80%9D%20It%E2%80%99s%20hard%20to%20see%20how%20he%20could%20have%20said%20anything%20else.%20But%20where%20does%20that%20leave%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20Saudi-Israel%20peace%20deal%20which%20the%20Joe%20Biden%20administration%20is%20so%20keen%20to%20broker%3F%20Is%20it%20dead%20in%20the%20water%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20only%20paused%20for%20a%20short%20duration%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E8)%20Very%20predictably%20the%20American%20government%20has%20announced%20its%20rock-solid%20unwavering%20support%20for%20Israel%20and%20Biden%20has%20rushed%20the%20US%20aircraft%20carrier%20Gerald%20Ford%20and%20other%20ships%20into%20the%20area%20presumably%20in%20a%20message%20to%20Iran%20and%20Hezbollah%20to%20exercise%20restraint.%20Is%20there%20a%20limit%20to%20how%20far%20Washington%20can%20go%20without%20adversely%20affecting%20its%20relationship%20with%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20UAE%3F%20After%20all%2C%20they%20are%20majority%20Muslim%20nations%20where%20public%20sentiment%20is%20not%20with%20Israel%20and%20they%20won%E2%80%99t%20like%20this%20display%20of%20American%20might.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E9)%20Now%20other%20than%20Israel%2C%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20nearest%20neighbour%20is%20Egypt.%20But%20Egypt%20was%20also%20the%20first%20Arab%20country%20to%20recognise%20Israel%20almost%2045%20years%20ago.%20But%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20policy%20that%E2%80%99s%20popular%20with%20the%20Egyptian%20people%20and%20the%20killing%20of%20Israeli%20terrorists%20in%20Alexandria%20has%20underlined%20that.%20How%20do%20you%20see%20Egypt%20handling%20this%20crisis%20on%20its%20borders%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E10)%20Finally%2C%20what%20impact%20will%20this%20have%20on%20Ukraine%3F%20So%20far%20it%E2%80%99s%20been%20the%20single%20focus%20of%20American%20and%20Western%20concern.%20That%20clearly%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20case.%20So%20has%20the%20Hamas-Israel%20crisis%20diminished%20the%20importance%20of%20Ukraine%20or%2C%20at%20least%2C%20reduced%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20and%20resources%20Washington%20can%20give%20to%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E11)%20One%20last%20question%3A%20How%20do%20you%20read%20the%20response%20from%20Beijing%20and%20Moscow%3F%20Beijing%20has%20called%20for%20de-escalation%20and%20a%20renewed%20focus%20on%20a%20two-nation%20solution.%20Moscow%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20said%20very%20much%20at%20all.%20Neither%20has%