d%20before%20the%20media%20to%20condemn%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20arrest%20rather%20than%20speak%20effusively%20about%20the%20bail%20and%20his%20%E2%80%98uprightness%E2%80%99%20makes%20him%20stand%20tall%20among%20the%20current%20crop%20of%20politicians%20for%20whom%20politics%20is%20all%20about%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20is%20torturing%20all%20regional%20parties%20which%20are%20doing%20good%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20extending%20solidarity%20to%20AAP%2C%20which%20is%20in%20crisis%20as%20three%20of%20its%20top%20leaders%20are%20currently%20imprisoned.%20%E2%80%9CI%20condemn%20the%20arrest%20of%20Sanjay%20Singh.%20The%20BJP%20is%20harassing%20the%20parties%20which%20are%20addressing%20the%20issues%20concerning%20the%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-rise-of-tejashwi-yadav-signals-significant-change-in-bihar-politics%5C%22%3EThe%20Rise%20of%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%20Signals%20Significant%20Change%20in%20Bihar%20Politics%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20BJP%20is%20frightened%20more%20at%20the%20release%20of%20the%20caste%20survey%20report%20in%20Bihar%20and%20Bihar%20government%20giving%20employment%20in%20lakhs%20to%20the%20youths.%20They%20(the%20BJP)%20are%20incapable%20of%20fighting%20a%20political%20battle.%20The%20only%20recourse%20they%20know%20is%20to%20misuse%20the%20central%20agencies%20against%20its%20opponents.%20But%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20fear.%20These%20diabolical%20moves%20will%20strengthen%20our%20resolve%20to%20defeat%20the%20BJP.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFollowing%20up%20on%20Tejashwi%E2%80%99s%20statements%2C%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20(RJD)%20MP%20and%20spokesperson%20Manoj%20Jha%20personally%20visited%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20family%20to%20extend%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20support.%20Although%20other%20constituent%20parties%20of%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20condemned%20the%20arrest%20of%20Singh%2C%20it%20was%20only%20the%20RJD%20which%20went%20a%20step%20further%20to%20send%20its%20representative%20to%20his%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3Cstrong%3ERJD-AAP%20relationship%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETejashwi%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20onslaught%20on%20AAP%20is%20sharply%20at%20variance%20with%20the%20cold%20relationship%20that%20his%20father%20and%20RJD%20chief%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20and%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20are%20known%20to%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELalu%20Yadav%20has%20been%20critical%20of%20AAP%20since%20the%20period%20it%20emerged%20from%20the%20Anna%20Hazare-led%20movement%20against%20corruption%20in%202014.%20Lalu%20has%20differences%20with%20Kejriwal%20and%20AAP%20for%20he%20perceives%20them%20as%20%E2%80%9Canti-Mandal%E2%80%9D%20and%20inimical%20to%20the%20battle%20for%20social%20justice.%20He%20also%20suspects%20that%20Kejriwal%20is%20closer%20to%20the%20Sangh%3Cem%3E%20parivar%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20philosophy%20which%20the%20former%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20detests.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKejriwal%20and%20most%20of%20his%20party%20men%2C%20including%20Sanjay%20Singh%2C%20were%20very%20critical%20of%20Lalu%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20corruption.%20They%20perceived%20that%20their%20association%20with%20the%20RJD%20in%20any%20manner%20would%20cost%20their%20credentials%20as%20%E2%80%98anti-corruption%E2%80%99%20crusaders%20%E2%80%93%20the%20plank%20on%20which%20it%20emerged%20on%20the%20political%20map.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20when%20Lalu%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Findia-news-india%2Fwhy-the-lalu-kejriwal-hug-became-a-controversy%2F%5C%22%3Ehugged%3C%2Fa%3E%20Kejriwal%20at%20a%20meeting%20(of%20Mahagathbandhan)%2C%20Kejriwal%20said%20openly%20that%20he%20did%20not%20like%20it.%20Lalu%20then%20responded%20by%20saying%20that%20it%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccourtesy%20of%20%5Ba%5D%20public%20stage%E2%80%9D%20while%20clarifying%20that%20there%20was%20no%20change%20of%20heart%20on%20his%20part%20in%20the%20way%20he%20viewed%20AAP.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F09170730%2FThe-Wire-36.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F09170730%2FThe-Wire-36.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F09170730%2FThe-Wire-36-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F09170730%2FThe-Wire-36-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-679120%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20and%20Arvind%20Kejriwal.%20Photos%3A%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20(Government%20of%20India%2FGODL%20License)%20and%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20(Government%20of%20the%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi%2FGODL%20License)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20Tejashwi%E2%80%99s%20approach%20to%20Kejriwal%20and%20AAP%20is%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20that%20of%20his%20father.%20It%20goes%20without%20saying%20that%20Kejriwal%20will%20rethink%20his%20and%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20the%20RJD%2C%20particularly%20after%20Tejashwi%E2%80%99s%20public%20show%20of%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20appears%20to%20have%20brought%20the%20RJD%20and%20AAP%20closer%20are%20the%20central%20investigating%20agencies%20%E2%80%93%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20and%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20%E2%80%93%20framing%20their%20leaders%20in%20corruption%20cases.%20Both%20parties%20say%20the%20cases%20represent%20a%20misuse%20of%20central%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20one%20day%20after%20the%20Rouse%20Avenue%20court%20granted%20bail%20to%20Tejashwi%20and%20the%20CBI%20arrested%20Sanjay%20Singh%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20questioned%20the%20CBI%20and%20ED%E2%80%99s%20charges%20against%20another%20AAP%20leader%20and%20former%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20of%20Delhi%20Manish%20Sisodia%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fno-money-has-come-to-manish-sisodia-how-will-you-bring-him-under-pmla-sc-to-ed%5C%22%3Estrong%20words%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CWhere%20is%20the%20proof%3F%20Where%20is%20the%20evidence%3F%20Except%20for%20the%20statement%20of%20Dinesh%20Arora%20(a%20businessman)%2C%20is%20there%20any%20other%20evidence%3F%20How%20will%20you%20bring%20Manish%20Sisodia%20under%20the%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%3F%E2%80%9D%20the%20top%20court%20said%20whilst%20hearing%20Sisodia%E2%80%99s%20bail%20plea.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20observation%20has%20created%20doubts%20about%20actions%20against%20the%20AAP%20leaders%2C%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20two%20central%20agencies%20have%20implicated%20Tejashwi%20in%20the%20land-for-job%20case%20is%20hardly%20convincing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20CBI%20and%20ED%2C%20some%20candidates%20obtained%20jobs%20in%20the%20railways%20in%20lieu%20of%20plots%20of%20land%20that%20they%20gave%20to%20Lalu%20when%20the%20latter%20was%20the%20minister%20for%20railways%20(2004-09).%20Tejashwi%20was%20a%20minor%20at%20that%20time%2C%20playing%20cricket%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Board%20of%20Cricket%20Control%20of%20India%20(BCCI)%E2%80%99s%20Under-15%20team%20and%20living%20away%20from%20the%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20CBI%20itself%20dropped%20these%20allegations%20in%202011%20after%20it%20had%20said%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Cno%20evidence%E2%80%9D%20to%20carry%20them%20forward.%20But%20the%20CBI%20and%20ED%20suddenly%20raided%20establishments%20connected%20to%20Lalu%20in%20Patna%20and%20Delhi%20in%202017%2C%20when%20Tejashwi%20was%20the%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20in%20the%20Nitish%20Kumar-led%20first%20Mahagathbandhan%20government%2C%20reopening%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcbi-tejashwi-yadav-lalu-prasad-nitish-bjp-jdu-rjd-irctc%5C%22%3ESo%20Why%20Is%20the%20CBI%20After%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%20Now%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20fell%20silent%20again%20for%20five%20years%20after%20Nitish%20broke%20away%20from%20the%20Mahagathbandhan%20and%20rejoined%20the%20BJP.%20However%2C%20they%20carried%20out%20raids%20on%20Lalu%20and%20his%20family%20members%20after%20Nitish%20returned%20to%20the%20Mahagathbandhan%20again%20in%20August%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIntriguingly%2C%20Tejashwi%20didn%E2%80%99t%20figure%20in%20the%20original%20chargesheet%20of%20the%20land-for-jobs%20scam%20case.%20But%20the%20CBI%20named%20him%20in%20the%20supplementary%20chargesheet%20filed%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETejashwi%E2%80%99s%20attributes%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETejashwi%20Yadav%20broadly%20appears%20to%20have%20three%20special%20attributes%20that%20contrast%20him%20with%20other%20young%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20his%20complete%20focus%20on%20the%20issues%20concerning%20the%20people.%20For%20example%2C%20during%20the%202020%20assembly%20elections%2C%20when%20he%20was%20fighting%20a%20lonely%20battle%20against%20the%20BJP-Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20with%20his%20father%20in%20jail%2C%20Tejashwi%20promised%2010%2C00%2C000%20jobs%20to%20the%20youth%20if%20his%20party%20was%20elected%20to%20power.%20He%20based%20his%20campaign%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20employment%20and%20outsmarted%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20%E2%80%93%20who%20addressed%20as%20many%20as%2031%20election%20rallies%20in%20Bihar%20at%20that%20time.%20Even%20though%20the%20RJD%20was%20unable%20to%20form%20the%20government%2C%20it%20emerged%20as%20the%20single%20largest%20party%20with%2078%20MLAs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F09%2F596103-lalu-tejaswi-pti.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20and%20Tejashwi%20Yadav.%20Credit%3A%20PTI%2FFiles%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-175013%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22360%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20and%20Tejashwi%20Yadav.%20Credit%3A%20PTI%2FFiles%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20as%20deputy%20CM%2C%20he%20has%20shown%20that%20he%20can%20implement%20what%20he%20promised.%20The%20Nitish%20Kumar%20government%20has%20already%20given%20over%20two%20lakh%20jobs%20since%20the%20Mahagathbandhan%20government%20was%20formed%20in%20August%20last%20year.%20Bihar%20is%20said%20to%20be%20far%20ahead%20of%20others%20in%20providing%20employment%20to%20the%20youth%2C%20whereas%20Modi%20and%20his%20Union%20government%20have%20failed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20he%20had%20joined%20hands%20with%20Nitish%20Kumar%20to%20ask%20for%20the%20caste-based%20census%20when%20he%20was%20in%20the%20opposition.%20Now%2C%20Bihar%20is%20the%20first%20state%20to%20have%20come%20out%20with%20the%20caste%20survey%20report%2C%20giving%20strength%20to%20INDIA%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20against%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20way%2C%20the%20young%20Tejashwi%20is%20quite%20sharp%20in%20identifying%20the%20issues%20that%20would%20succeed%20against%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20gargantuan%20election%20machine.%20Secondly%2C%20he%20is%20bold%2C%20a%20trait%20that%20he%20has%20inherited%20from%20his%20father.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20personally%20went%20to%20express%20support%20to%20West%20Bengal%20chief%20minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20during%20the%202021%20assembly%20elections%2C%20when%20Modi%20had%20mocked%20Mamata%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EDidi-o-Didi%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20investigating%20agencies%20were%20after%20her%20party%E2%80%99s%20top%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMamata%20was%20overwhelmed%20by%20his%20support%20at%20the%20time%20when%20political%20leaders%20from%20other%20parties%20acted%20diplomatically%20to%20avoid%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98wrath%E2%80%99.%20As%20a%20railway%20minister%2C%20she%20had%20tabled%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Fmagazine%2Ffocus%2Fstory%2Flalu-vs-mamata-whos-right-17676-2010-01-11%5C%22%3EWhite%20Paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20Lalu%E2%80%99s%20tenure.%20But%20when%20she%20came%20to%20attend%20the%20first%20conclave%20of%20the%20opposition%20parties%20in%20August%2C%20she%20bowed%20down%20before%20Lalu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20Tejashwi%E2%80%99s%20third%20but%20equally%20important%20attribute%20is%20deference%20to%20elders.%20He%20has%20the%20utmost%20respect%20for%20Nitish%2C%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20contemporary%2C%20and%20avoids%20speaking%20when%20he%20is%20with%20the%20chief%20minister.%20He%20touches%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20feet%20whenever%20he%20goes%20out%20of%20home%20and%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENalin%20Verma%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%2C%20author%2C%20media%20educator%2C%20and%20independent%20researcher%20in%20folklore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696943735000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F24105952%2F2022_8img22_Aug_2022_PTI08_22_2022_000199B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftejashwi-yadav-stands-apart-today-young-politicians%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20of%20Bihar%20has%20already%20proved%20his%20mettle%20in%20taking%20on%20the%20BJP.%20He%20is%20poised%20for%20bigger%20things%20given%20his%20ability%20to%20connect%20with%20masses%20that%20few%20other%20leaders%20of%20his%20age%20can%20match.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A71%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftejashwi-yadav-stands-apart-today-young-politicians%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Guatemala%20paralysed%20as%20pro-democracy%20protests%20run%20into%20second%20week%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696943452000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F4BD0%2Fproduction%2F_131380491_660bcca5b1f554e5a38d9d511fb217b07a2ff7920_0_2048_13671000x667.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-latin-america-67064814%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Protesters%20are%20demanding%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20attorney-general%2C%20whom%20they%20accuse%20of%20undermining%20democracy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A233%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-latin-america-67064814%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-latin-america-67064814.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-latin-america-67064814.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Marginalities%20Aren%E2%80%99t%20Hermetically%20Sealed.%20The%20Decade-Old%20'NALSA'%20Judgment%20Ignores%20This%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F10160824%2F3667997607_a1f6bde5f8_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBefore%20we%20get%20to%20celebrating%20a%20decade%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20in%20the%202014%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENational%20Legal%20Services%20Authority%20(NALSA)%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20case%20in%20April%20next%20year%2C%20we%20should%20look%20at%20the%20problems%20in%20the%20representation%20of%20marginalities%20and%20the%20role%20played%20by%20the%20empty%20rhetoric%20of%20analogies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20opening%20paragraph%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20states%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9C%5BO%5Dur%20society%20often%20ridicules%20and%20abuses%20the%20Transgender%20community%20and%20in%20public%20places%20like%20railway%20stations%2C%20bus%20stands%2C%20schools%2C%20workplaces%2C%20malls%2C%20theatres%2C%20hospitals%2C%20they%20are%20sidelined%20and%20treated%20as%20untouchables.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20underlying%20assumption%20of%20this%20analogy%20is%20that%20transgender%20and%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchable%E2%80%9D%20persons%20are%20two%20marginalised%20groups%20distinct%20from%20each%20other.%20The%20assumption%20fails%20in%20the%20face%20of%20Dalit%20and%20Adivasi%20transgender%20persons%20such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.roundtableindia.co.in%2Ftransgender-and-caste-lived-experience-transphobia-as-a-form-of-brahminism-an-interview-of-living-smile-vidya%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ELiving%20Smile%20Vidya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftelanganatoday.com%2Fspecially-abled-kiran-nayak-striving-for-transgender-rights%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKiran%20Nayak%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1055658%2Fmeet-dalit-transgender-activist-grace-banu-who-campaigns-for-reservations-for-transgender-people%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGrace%20Banu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERhetorical%20claims%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20%E2%80%98transgender%20persons%20are%20treated%20as%20untouchables%E2%80%99%20imply%20that%20marginalised%20groups%20are%20placed%20in%20mutually%20exclusive%20either-or%20sets.%20The%20emerging%20understanding%20of%20one%20group%20is%20said%20to%20be%20just%20like%20the%20previously%20existing%20understanding%20of%20another.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20%E2%80%9CGay%20is%20the%20new%20black%E2%80%9D%20is%20an%20example%20of%20a%20rhetorical%20claim%20that%20set%20apart%20gay%20persons%20from%20black%20persons%2C%20as%20if%C2%A0%20all%20gay%20persons%20were%20posited%20as%20white.%20Not%20only%20was%20this%20empirically%20false%2C%20it%20channelled%20a%20discursive%20understanding%20of%20one%20marginality%20into%20another.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20rhetorical%20claims%20and%20distortions%20are%20amplified%20within%20legal%20movements%C2%A0%20As%20a%20result%2C%20a%20group%20recognised%20as%20discriminated%20against%20is%20disabled%20from%20representing%20a%20newly%20emerging%20group%2C%20also%20discriminated%20against.%20Rhetoric%20and%20analogies%20generate%20blind%20spots%20that%20make%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchable%E2%80%9D%20transgender%20persons%20invisible%2C%20and%20also%20disable%20their%20representational%20agency%20as%20%E2%80%9Cclass%20representatives.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Untouchable%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20considered%20the%20reality%20of%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchable%E2%80%9D%20transgender%20persons%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20it%20would%20have%20seen%20an%20overlapping%20function%20of%20caste%2C%20sex%2C%20and%20gender%20categories.%20The%20court%20would%20have%20considered%20some%20of%20the%20similarities%20and%20differences%20between%20the%20emerging%20legal%20understanding%20of%20the%20third%20gender%20and%20the%20existing%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SC)%20categories.%20The%20two%20categories%20could%20be%20said%20to%20be%20similar%2C%20because%20both%20gender%20and%20caste%20are%20assigned%20at%20birth.%20They%20are%20different%20because%20gender%20categories%20can%20be%20legally%20changed%2C%20whereas%20the%20SC%20categories%20cannot%20be%20changed.%20This%20characteristic%20has%20significance%20in%20the%20doctrinal%20understanding%20of%20anti-discrimination%20law.%20Some%20categories%20are%20so%20immutable%20that%20the%20discriminated-against%20groups%20cannot%20choose%20to%20opt%20out%20of%20the%20categories%20to%20which%20they%20are%20assigned.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20about%20these%20similarities%20and%20differences%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EForemost%2C%20in%20its%20omission%20of%20caste%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20lost%20a%20potential%20to%20learn%20from%20the%20existing%20legal%20discourse%20on%20caste%2C%20class%2C%20and%20affirmative%20action.%20Amid%20other%20post-colonial%20continuities%2C%20the%20legal%20idea%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbackwardness%E2%80%9D%20finds%20explicit%20yet%20undefined%20mention%20in%20Article%2016(4)%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20which%20allows%20the%20state%20to%20make%20provisions%20for%20reservations%20in%20public%20employment%20in%20the%20favour%20of%20the%20backward%20classes%20of%20citizens.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20was%20no%20doctrinal%20requirement%20of%20comparing%20transgender%20persons%20with%20untouchables.%20Alarge%20bench%20of%20nine%20judges%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndra%20Sawhney%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1992)%20is%20sufficiently%20instructive%20in%20the%20matter%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20necessary%20for%20a%20class%20to%20be%20designated%20as%20a%20backward%20class%20that%20it%20%5Bbe%5D%20situated%20similarly%20to%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes%2FScheduled%20Tribes%E2%80%9D%20(Para.%20126).%20Thus%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20demonstrated%20insufficient%20familiarity%20with%2C%20and%20complete%20disregard%20for%2C%20a%20larger%20bench%20and%20a%20precedent%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndra%20Sawhney%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flgbtqia%2Ftransgender-prisoners-india%5C%22%3EMisgendering%2C%20Sexual%20Violence%2C%20Harassment%3A%20What%20it%20Is%20to%20Be%20a%20Transgender%20Person%20in%20an%20Indian%20Prison%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%202014%20also%20did%20not%20explain%20why%20these%20analogies%20were%20being%20made.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWas%20it%20for%20an%20eventual%20recognition%20and%20declaration%20of%20transgender%20persons%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbackward%20class%3F%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWho%20decides%20this%20legal%20status%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbackwardness%2C%E2%80%9D%20how%2C%20and%20to%20what%20effect%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIs%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchability%E2%80%9D%20the%20same%20as%20%E2%80%9Cbackwardness%3F%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDoes%20this%20backwardness%20require%20parity%20of%20status%20with%20persons%20in%20the%20SC%20categories%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWho%20among%20the%20marginalised%20can%20represent%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERather%20than%20inform%20itself%20of%20a%20legal%20discourse%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndra%20Sawhney%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1992)%20that%20was%20binding%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20informed%20by%20arguments%20based%20on%20more%20dominant%20frameworks%20of%20caste%2C%20sex%2C%20and%20gender.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20National%20Legal%20Services%20Authority%20(NALSA)%20as%20the%20first%20petitioner%2C%20there%20were%20a%20few%20%E2%80%9Cimpleadment%20applications%2C%E2%80%9D%20including%20one%20from%20a%20Hijra%20activist%20by%20the%20name%20of%20Laxmi%20Narayan%20Tripathy%20%E2%80%93%20a%20name%20that%20discloses%20the%20applicant%E2%80%99s%20caste%20denomination%20as%20Brahmin%2C%20the%20highest%20echelon%20of%20caste-based%20hierarchies.%20This%20is%20significant%20for%20an%20understanding%20of%20how%20certain%20dominant%20segments%20within%20minority%20groups%20were%20privileged%20as%20%E2%80%9Cclass%20representatives%E2%80%9D%20in%20an%20emerging%20legal%20discourse.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERegardless%20of%20any%20explicit%20self-identification%20on%20the%20part%20of%20Tripathy%2C%20caste%20associations%20and%20identities%20are%20enmeshed%20and%20encoded%20within%20some%20surnames%20%E2%80%93%20such%20that%20their%20reception%20goes%20beyond%20any%20self-awareness%2C%20declaration%2C%20intent%2C%20and%20consciousness.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHad%20the%20court%20been%20alert%20to%20this%20salience%20of%20caste%20in%20naming%2C%20it%20would%20have%20noted%20a%20contradiction%20of%20sorts%20%E2%80%93%20a%20certain%20reverse%20mobility%20of%20caste-based%20hierarchies%20%E2%80%93%20that%20allowed%20a%20Brahmin%20to%20be%20similarly%20situated%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchable.%E2%80%9D%20An%20imminent%20contradiction%20in%20this%20analogy%20is%20especially%20ironic%20in%20a%20caste-based%20hierarchy%20that%20accords%20the%20highest%20stature%20to%20Brahmins%20and%20the%20lowest%20stature%20to%20%E2%80%9Cuntouchables.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20lack%20of%20any%20explicit%20labelling%20or%20signage%20of%20this%20Brahmin%20identity%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20arguments%20of%20Tripathy%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20were%20aligned%20with%20well-known%20Brahmanical%20ideas.%20The%20intervention%20foregrounded%20a%20more%20favourable%20historical%20background%20of%20transgender%20persons%20within%20Hindu%20mythology%2C%20Vedic%2C%20and%20Puranic%20literatures%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%202014%3A%20Para.%206)%2C%20which%20are%20also%20considered%20historically%20exclusive%20knowledge-domains%20of%20the%20Brahmins%20and%20sources%20of%20pervasive%20caste%20and%20gender-based%20inequality%20(such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EManusmriti%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E).%20Tripathy%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20made%20references%20to%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20repealed%20Criminal%20Tribes%20Act%2C%201871%20and%20%E2%80%A6%20the%20inhuman%20manner%20by%20which%20they%20were%20treated%20at%20the%20time%20of%20a%20British%20Colonial%20rule%E2%80%9D%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%202014%3A%20Para.%206).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20endorsed%20and%20validated%20these%20arguments%20by%20further%20elaborating%20on%20them%20(2014%3A%20Paras.%2012%E2%80%9317).%20This%20was%20a%20selective%20foregrounding%20of%20the%20ills%20of%20colonial%20oppression%2C%20while%20neglecting%20and%20remaining%20silent%20about%20the%20historic%20ills%20of%20caste-based%20subordination%20and%20inequality.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmarriage-equality-legal-recognition%5C%22%3EA%20Trans-Queer%20Paradox%20and%20the%20Search%20for%20Legal%20Recognition%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20level%20of%20a%20failed%20eventual%20outcome%2C%20%3Ci%3ENALSA%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%99s%20declaration%20of%20transgender%20persons%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csocially%20and%20educationally%20backward%20class%E2%80%9D%20failed%20to%20be%20recognised%20in%20the%20legislative%20framework%20to%20follow%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupriyo-marriage-equality-supreme-court-solicitor-general%5C%22%3ETransgender%20Persons%20(Protection%20of%20Rights)%20Act%20of%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20perhaps%20because%20the%20identification%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbackward%20classes%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20constitutional%20function%20of%20the%20governments%20at%20the%20federal%20and%20state%20levels%2C%20not%20the%20judiciary.%20In%20an%20eagerness%20to%20declare%20affirmative%20action%20for%20transgender%20persons%2C%20%3Ci%3ENALSA%3C%2Fi%3E%20appropriated%20a%20function%20of%20the%20executive%20branch%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20juridical%20thinking%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENALSA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20an%20illustration%20of%20an%20analogy%20drawn%20from%20anti-caste%20discourse%20and%20a%20failure%20to%20engage%20with%20that%20discourse.%20Analogies%2C%20and%20assertions%20of%20identities%2C%20must%20engage%20with%20surrounding%20discourses%20for%20an%20improved%20understanding%20of%20marginalization%20and%20for%20generating%20more%20inclusive%20discourses%20on%20matters%20of%20representations%2C%20recognition%2C%20and%20intersectional%20solidarities%20worldwide.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EProfessor%20Dr%20Sumit%20Baudh%20(they%20%2Fhe)%20teaches%20Caste%2C%20Law%20and%20Representation%2C%20among%20other%20courses%20and%20sources.%20Views%20in%20this%20article%20are%C2%A0%20drawn%20from%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F14754835.2020.1858402%5C%22%3Elonger%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20an%20academic%20journal.%20He%20tweets%20%40BaudhSumit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696942839000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F10160824%2F3667997607_a1f6bde5f8_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fcaste-gender-queer-nalsa-judgment-transgender%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Reading%20a%20marginality%20through%20the%20marginality%20of%20another%20(even%20if%20intersecting)%20group%20can%20fail%20to%20do%20something%20crucial%20in%20matters%20of%20representation%20and%20recognition.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fcaste-gender-queer-nalsa-judgment-transgender%22%2C%22cdnAmpUr