ohli-Nagarathna%20bench%20on%20Monday%2C%20in%20view%20of%20the%20AIIMS%20doctors%E2%80%99%20moral%20dilemma%20to%20terminate%20a%20viable%20pregnancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%2C%20after%20a%20brief%20hearing%20at%204%20pm%2C%20asked%20Bhati%20to%20submit%20a%20written%20application%20for%20recall%20so%20that%20the%20same%20bench%20which%20passed%20the%20order%20for%20abortion%20on%20Monday%20could%20be%20requested%20to%20consider%20it%20on%20Wednesday%20morning.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20an%20unprecedented%20hearing%20twice%20%E2%80%93%20once%20in%20the%20morning%20and%20again%20in%20the%20afternoon%20%E2%80%93%20to%20hear%20the%20pregnant%20married%20woman%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3Ewho%20did%20not%20want%20to%20proceed%20with%20her%20third%20pregnancy%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20she%20would%20not%20be%20mentally%20fit%20to%20foster%20the%20child.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Kohli%20and%20Nagarathna%20spoke%20to%20the%20petitioner-mother%20and%20her%20husband%20online%2C%20to%20ascertain%20her%20wishes%20and%20satisfy%20the%20court%20that%20the%20couple%20voluntarily%20opted%20to%20abort%20the%20child%2C%20despite%20the%20AIIMS%20Medical%20Board%20certifying%20that%20the%20pregnancy%20is%20viable.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner-woman%20who%20sought%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20to%20abort%20her%20pregnancy%20in%20view%20of%20Section%203(2)%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.mohfw.gov.in%2F%3Fq%3Dacts-rules-and-standards-health-sector%2Facts%2Fmtp-act-1971%5C%22%3EMedical%20Termination%20of%20Pregnancy%20(MTP)%20Act%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20permits%20abortion%20only%20before%2020%20weeks%20of%20pregnancy%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20%E2%80%9Crisk%20of%20grave%20injury%20to%20the%20mother%E2%80%99s%20physical%20or%20mental%20health%20or%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20there%20is%20a%20substantial%20risk%20that%20the%20child%20would%20suffer%20from%20physical%20or%20mental%20abnormalities%20to%20be%20seriously%20handicapped%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20she%20was%20suffering%20from%20lactational%20amenorrhea%20(which%20causes%20a%20temporary%20absence%20of%20menstruation%20in%20lactating%20mothers)%20and%20post-partum%20depression%20(a%20medical%20condition%20that%20many%20women%20experience%20after%20having%20a%20baby%2C%20with%20feelings%20of%20sadness%2C%20anxiety%20and%20tiredness).%20The%20couple%20is%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20raise%20a%20third%20child%20because%20of%20family%20and%20financial%20conditions%2C%20the%20petitioner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20took%20note%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20first%20child%20of%20the%20couple%20is%20four%20years%20old%2C%20while%20the%20second%20child%20is%20one%20year%20old.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20outset%2C%20the%20bench%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20it%20was%20concerned%20more%20about%20the%20mother%E2%80%99s%20health%20and%20not%20that%20of%20the%20child.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20wanted%20to%20understand%20the%20context%2C%20that%20is%2C%20this%20is%20the%20case%20of%20a%20married%20couple%2C%20and%20not%20one%20of%20forced%20pregnancy.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20added%20that%20it%20had%20no%20issue%20if%20the%20mother%20wanted%20to%20continue%20her%20pregnancy%2C%20but%20it%20underlined%20that%20she%20must%20have%20the%20willpower%20and%20emotional%20strength%20to%20do%20so.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20observed%20that%20the%20state%20is%20not%20going%20to%20help%20her%20after%20the%20delivery%20of%20the%20child%2C%20which%20is%20a%20result%20of%20the%20failure%20of%20family%20planning%20methods.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20morning%20hearing%2C%20the%20bench%20observed%20that%20the%20pregnancy%20is%20sought%20to%20be%20aborted%20to%20avoid%20giving%20birth%20to%20an%20unwanted%20child.%20The%20bench%20decided%20to%20give%20time%20till%201%20pm%20to%20ascertain%20whether%20the%20mother%20wants%20to%20continue%20her%20pregnancy.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%201%20pm%2C%20the%20petitioner%20made%20it%20clear%20to%20the%20bench%20through%20an%20online%20interaction%20that%20she%20was%20in%20favour%20of%20abortion%2C%20despite%20doctors%E2%80%99%20advice%20that%20she%20could%20give%20the%20child%20for%20adoption%20after%20delivery%20since%20the%20pregnancy%20is%20viable.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20took%20note%20of%20the%20contention%20that%20after%20the%2025th%20week%20of%20pregnancy%2C%20the%20choice%20of%20the%20mother%20could%20not%20be%20exercised%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20viable%20baby.%20But%20the%20bench%20emphasised%20that%20giving%20the%20child%20to%20adoption%20should%20also%20be%20the%20choice%20of%20the%20petitioner-mother.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20the%20mother%20clearly%20said%20no%20to%20giving%20the%20child%20to%20adoption.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20found%20merit%20in%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20argument%20through%20her%20counsel%20that%20she%20was%20asking%20for%20her%20rights%20under%20Article%2021%20(protection%20of%20life%20and%20personal%20liberty)%2C%20which%20overrides%20the%20MTP%20Act.%20The%20additional%20solicitor%20general%2C%20Aishwarya%20Bhati%2C%20submitted%20that%20the%20bench%20had%20to%20balance%20the%20autonomy%20of%20the%20woman%20over%20her%20body%20with%20the%20right%20of%20the%20viable%20baby.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20took%20note%20of%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20Medical%20Board%20that%20the%20baby%20is%20viable%2C%20and%20can%20survive%20outside%20the%20mother%E2%80%99s%20womb%2C%20and%20there%20is%20a%20reasonable%20chance%20of%20survival%20of%20the%20child.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F02135757%2Fezgif.com-webp-to-jpg.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ayushman%20Bharat%2C%20health%20and%20wellness%20centres%2C%20union%20budget%202020%2C%20health%20budget%2C%20public%20healthcare%2C%20private%20healthcare%2C%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%2C%20AIIMS%2C%20NIMHANS%2C%20PGIMER%2C%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Jan%20Arogya%20Yojana%2C%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Development%20Plan%20for%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20Regional%20Institute%20of%20Nursing%20and%20Paramedical%20Science%20Aizawl%2C%20nursing%2C%20nurses%2C%20hospital%20staff%2C%20National%20Health%20Policy%2C%20National%20Health%20Mission%2C%20primary%20care%2C%20secondary%20care%2C%20tertiary%20care%2C%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F02135757%2Fezgif.com-webp-to-jpg.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F02135757%2Fezgif.com-webp-to-jpg-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F02135757%2Fezgif.com-webp-to-jpg-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-393168%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAIIMS%2C%20Delhi.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bench%20wanted%20to%20know%20whether%20there%20is%20a%20reasonable%20chance%20of%20living%20for%20the%20child%20with%20dignity%20and%20nutrition%20and%20whether%20the%20couple%20can%20provide%20that.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20can%E2%80%99t%20force%20the%20petitioner-mother%20to%20give%20the%20child%20up%20for%20adoption%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20told%20the%20ASG%2C%20who%20contended%20that%20her%20right%20of%20autonomy%20ends%20once%20the%20fetus%20is%20viable.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20that%20although%20the%20Medical%20Board%20opined%20that%20the%20child%20can%20survive%20if%20born%2C%20there%20is%20a%20chance%20of%20harm%20to%20the%20child%20because%20of%20the%20medicine%20that%20the%20petitioner-mother%20has%20been%20taking%20to%20treat%20her%20depression.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20husband%20told%20the%20bench%20that%20if%20she%20had%20to%20give%20birth%20to%20the%20child%2C%20they%20would%20rear%20it%2C%20and%20not%20give%20it%20for%20adoption%2C%20though%20he%20is%20concerned%20about%20her%20depression.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20wife%20should%20not%20suffer%2C%20and%20the%20child%20should%20not%20suffer%20from%20any%20abnormalities%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20the%20bench.%20He%20said%20that%20as%20the%20Medical%20Board%20is%20silent%20on%20the%20child%E2%80%99s%20condition%2C%20they%20cannot%20take%20care%20of%20the%20child%20if%20it%20is%20not%20healthy.%20As%20there%20is%20a%20risk%20that%20the%20child%2C%20if%20born%2C%20may%20be%20unwell%2C%20the%20couple%20preferred%20to%20abort%20the%20fetus.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBalancing%20of%20rights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20told%20the%20ASG%20that%20there%20is%20no%20competing%20right%20of%20an%20unborn%20child%20to%20be%20balanced%20with%20that%20of%20the%20petitioner-mother.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20held%20that%20it%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20citizens%20to%20adopt%20family%20planning%20methods%20to%20avoid%20giving%20birth%20to%20an%20unwanted%20child.%20The%20couple%20has%20a%20responsibility%20and%20can%E2%80%99t%20produce%20children%20like%20this%2C%20the%20bench%20observed%2C%20as%20it%20constitutes%20a%20burden%20on%20the%20country.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20ASG%20pleaded%20with%20the%20bench%20to%20adjourn%20the%20hearing%20till%20Tuesday%2C%20to%20enable%20her%20to%20make%20submissions%20on%20balancing%20the%20right%20to%20life%20with%20the%20autonomy%20of%20the%20woman%20over%20her%20body.%20The%20ASG%20submitted%20that%20there%20can%20be%20no%20absolute%20right%20of%20autonomy%20of%20a%20woman%20over%20her%20body.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bench%20disagreed%20and%20said%20even%20a%20day%E2%80%99s%20delay%20would%20mean%20a%20setback%20to%20the%20mother.%20The%20bench%20was%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20child%20may%20not%20survive%2C%20if%20born%2C%20even%20if%20it%20is%20kept%20in%20incubation.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20bench%20decided%20to%20give%20priority%20to%20the%20petitioner-mother%E2%80%99s%20mental%20health.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20reasoned%20that%20it%20has%20expansively%20interpreted%20Section%205%20of%20the%20MTP%20Act%20as%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cmental%20health%E2%80%9D%20has%20a%20broader%20connotation%20than%20%E2%80%9Cmental%20illness%E2%80%9D.%20Due%20to%20a%20delay%20in%20recognising%20pregnancy%20and%20changes%20in%20life%20circumstances%2C%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20pregnancy%20has%20become%20unwanted%20and%20unviable%2C%20the%20bench%20concluded.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20held%20that%20it%20took%20into%20account%20the%20decisional%20autonomy%20of%20the%20mother%20%E2%80%93%20including%20her%20physical%2C%20mental%2C%20financial%20and%20socio-economic%20background.%20The%20court%20has%20recognised%20the%20right%20of%20a%20woman%20over%20her%20body%2C%20and%20an%20unwanted%20child%20results%20in%20imposing%20the%20responsibility%20of%20rearing%20on%20the%20mother%2C%20when%20she%20does%20not%20consider%20herself%20fit%20to%20bear%20the%20onerous%20responsibility%2C%20the%20bench%20concluded.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20directed%20that%20in%20the%20event%20of%20the%20procedure%20for%20abortion%20to%20be%20carried%20out%20on%20Tuesday%20morning%20resulting%20in%20the%20birth%20of%20the%20live%20child%2C%20it%20should%20be%20kept%20in%20incubation%2C%20and%20may%20be%20given%20in%20adoption%2C%20if%20advisable.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20reluctant%20to%20entertain%20petitions%20under%20Article%2032%2C%20when%20the%20petitioner%20had%20the%20option%20of%20approaching%20the%20high%20court%20for%20an%20efficacious%20remedy%20under%20Article%20226%20of%20the%20constitution.%20However%2C%20as%20time%20was%20running%20out%2C%20it%20was%20deemed%20appropriate%20to%20entertain%20her%20petition%2C%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221156%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01.jpg%201156w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01-300x187.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02102630%2F1156px-Supreme_Court_of_India_01-1024x638.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671125%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Central%20Wing%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20Photo%3A%20Subhashish%20Panigrahi%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELessons%20on%20family%20planning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20that%20the%20present%20case%20has%20valuable%20lessons%20for%20married%20couples%2C%20who%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20more%20cautious%2C%20in%20preventing%20unplanned%20pregnancies%20by%20adopting%20family%20planning%20methods.%20As%20India%20is%20the%20most%20populated%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%20striving%20to%20achieve%20socio-economic%20development%20within%20the%20limited%20means%20and%20resources%20that%20the%20state%20has%2C%20every%20couple%20has%20equal%20rights%20and%20obligations%20including%20that%20of%20rearing%20children%20with%20access%20to%20nutrition%2C%20good%20education%2C%20the%20court%20said.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20underlined%20the%20need%20to%20disseminate%20all%20the%20schemes%20floated%20by%20Central%20and%20state%20family%20planning%20agencies%20to%20avoid%20unwanted%20pregnancies%20in%20married%20couples%20so%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20adoption%20of%20adequate%20family%20planning%20measures%20does%20not%20result%20in%20a%20case%20like%20this.%20The%20bench%20learnt%20that%20the%20couple%20in%20this%20case%20was%20not%20aware%20of%20family%20planning%2C%20and%20didn%E2%80%99t%20take%20adequate%20care%20to%20prevent%20an%20unwanted%20pregnancy.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20noted%20the%20silver%20lining%20in%20this%20case%2C%20as%20the%20mother-in-law%20of%20the%20petitioner%20supports%20the%20daughter-in-law%20in%20rearing%20her%20children.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20today%E2%80%99s%20urban%20nuclear%20family%2C%20joint%20family%20is%20mostly%20missing%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20noted%20in%20its%20order.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20is%20not%20a%20forced%20pregnancy%2C%20the%20petitioner-mother%20has%20valid%20reasons%20to%20avoid%20an%20unwanted%20pregnancy%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20the%20bench%20directed%20AIIMS%20to%20carry%20out%20her%20abortion%20on%20Tuesday%20morning%2C%20as%20desired%20by%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20reasons%20to%20be%20recorded%20separately%2C%20we%20allow%20the%20present%20writ%20petition%20with%20a%20direction%20issued%20to%20the%20petitioner%20to%20visit%20the%20Obstetrics%20and%20Gynaecology%20Department%2C%20AIIMS%2C%20New%20Delhi%20tomorrow%20morning%2C%20i.e.%2C%20on%2010th%20October%2C%202023.%C2%A0%20AIIMS%20shall%20admit%20the%20petitioner%20for%20her%20to%20undergo%20the%20procedure%20of%20termination%20of%20her%20pregnancy%20at%20the%20earliest%20with%20follow%20up%20as%20may%20be%20advised%20by%20the%20treating%20doctors.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696939236000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F18171021%2Fpregnant-woman-under-cloudy-sky-in-silhouette-photography-1717292.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-seeks-recall-of-scs-order-permitting-married-woman-to-terminate-26-week-pregnancy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20AIIMS%20doctors%20expressed%20their%20inability%20to%20terminate%20a%20viable%20pregnancy%2C%20the%20government%20sought%20the%20recall%20of%20the%20order%20passed%20on%20Monday%20granting%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20plea%20for%20abortion%20on%20mental%20health%20grounds.%20The%20same%20bench%20will%20consider%20the%20recall%20application%20on%C2%A0Wednesday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-seeks-recall-of-scs-order-permitting-married-woman-to-terminate-26-week-pregnancy%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Remembering%20Jagjit%20on%20his%20death%20anniversary%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696939140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104316968%2Cimgsize-17770.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fmusic%2Fnews%2Fremembering-jagjit-singh-on-his-death-anniversary-shefali-shahs-soulful-rendition-of-his-nazm-in-once-again%2Farticleshow%2F104317007.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg